# Add Prisma Migration — Procedure

Prisma Migrate only — **no raw SQL** in application code ([CODE-004]). Schema truth: `docs/02_DATABASE_SCHEMA.md`; conventions → `15-backend-database-prisma.mdc`.

## Step 0: Preconditions

- [ ] Entity/column design matches `docs/02_DATABASE_SCHEMA.md` and `docs/01_DOMAIN_MODEL.md`.
- [ ] Enum values align with `packages/shared` (`Role`, `HomebrewStatus`, etc.).
- [ ] Breaking change assessed — production data impact noted in PR.
- [ ] Docker Postgres running: `docker compose up -d` (`docs/09` Bölüm 2).

Load: `docs/02_DATABASE_SCHEMA.md`, `docs/09_DEV_WORKFLOW.md` Bölüm 8, `docs/01_DOMAIN_MODEL.md` (if new entity).

## Step 1: Edit schema.prisma

Path: `apps/api/prisma/schema.prisma`.

Naming rules:

| Layer | Convention | Example |
| --- | --- | --- |
| PostgreSQL table | `snake_case` plural | `campaign_members` |
| Prisma model | `PascalCase` | `CampaignMember` |
| TS field | `camelCase` | `ownerId` |
| Mapping | `@@map`, `@map` | `@map("owner_id")` |

```prisma
model Campaign {
  id          String   @id @default(uuid())
  ownerId     String   @map("owner_id")
  name        String
  createdAt   DateTime @default(now()) @map("created_at")
  updatedAt   DateTime @updatedAt @map("updated_at")
  owner       User     @relation(fields: [ownerId], references: [id])
  members     CampaignMember[]

  @@map("campaigns")
}
```

Checklist:

```
[ ] UUID PK @default(uuid()) unless composite PK (members, collection_items)
[ ] created_at on every table; updated_at on mutable tables
[ ] FK onDelete matches docs/02 Bölüm 4 cascade table
[ ] Indexes for owner_id, campaign_id, foreign keys used in policy queries
[ ] JSONB fields documented in domain model (no DB-level JSON schema)
```

## Step 2: Create and Apply Migration (Local)

```bash
pnpm --filter api prisma migrate dev --name <kebab-case-description>
```

Examples (`docs/09` Bölüm 8):

```bash
pnpm --filter api prisma migrate dev --name add-campaign-setting-field
pnpm --filter api prisma migrate dev --name create-dm-notes-table
```

`migrate dev`:

1. Generates SQL under `apps/api/prisma/migrations/<timestamp>_<name>/`
2. Applies to local DB
3. Regenerates Prisma Client

**Review generated SQL** before commit — unexpected drops or locks.

## Step 3: Update Domain Docs (if new entity)

If migration introduces new tables or meaningful columns:

- [ ] `docs/02_DATABASE_SCHEMA.md` — table definition
- [ ] `docs/01_DOMAIN_MODEL.md` — entity rules, state machine
- [ ] `docs/03_API_CONTRACTS.md` — if endpoints expose new fields

Same PR as migration when possible.

## Step 4: Seed Compatibility

```bash
pnpm --filter api prisma db seed
```

Seed path: `apps/api/prisma/seed.ts` (`docs/09` Bölüm 9).

```
[ ] Seed runs without error after migration
[ ] New NOT NULL columns have default or seed populates them
[ ] Official 5e reference seed still loads
[ ] Admin seed account still created
```

If seed breaks → fix seed in **same PR**.

## Step 5: Application Code Updates

After client regenerate:

1. Update services/DTOs/types using new fields.
2. Add factories in `apps/api/test/factories/` for new models.
3. Update `afterEach` truncate order if new FK tables (`docs/08` Bölüm 4.2).

## Step 6: Enum Changes

PostgreSQL native enums via Prisma — adding values needs careful migration:

```bash
pnpm --filter api prisma migrate dev --name add-homebrew-status-value
```

Verify SQL uses `ALTER TYPE ... ADD VALUE`. Coordinate with `packages/shared` enum.

## Step 7: Integration Test DB

Test setup runs `prisma migrate deploy` against `TEST_DATABASE_URL`:

```bash
pnpm --filter api test -- --ci
```

Fresh clone sanity:

```bash
docker compose down -v && docker compose up -d
pnpm --filter api prisma migrate dev
pnpm --filter api prisma db seed
```

## Step 8: Staging / Production Apply

**Never** `migrate dev` in production.

```bash
pnpm --filter api prisma migrate deploy
```

CI/CD deploy step runs `migrate deploy` only (`docs/09` Bölüm 8).

## Step 9: Rollback Strategy

Prisma has **no automatic down migration**.

| Scenario | Action |
| --- | --- |
| Migration not yet merged | delete migration folder, reset local DB, recreate |
| Already deployed | new forward migration `revert-<name>` reversing change |
| Failed mid-apply | `prisma migrate resolve --rolled-back <name>` then fix |

Critical data risk → PITR ([INF-OPEN-3] — human decision, no agent assumption).

## Step 10: PR Requirements

Per `docs/09` Bölüm 8:

```
[ ] Migration SQL committed under prisma/migrations/
[ ] PR describes tables/columns added/changed/removed
[ ] Prefer migration-only PR when large schema change
[ ] seed verified
[ ] docs/02 updated if schema doc drifted
```

Commit message example:

```
feat(db): add dm_notes table with sort_order column
```

## Anti-patterns

- ❌ `$executeRaw` / string-concat SQL for normal CRUD
- ❌ Manual DB edits without migration file
- ❌ camelCase column names in PostgreSQL
- ❌ Migration bundled with unrelated feature without justification
- ❌ Skipping seed verification

## When to Split PRs

| Case | Recommendation |
| --- | --- |
| Large schema + feature | Migration PR first, feature PR second |
| Small additive column + endpoint | Same PR acceptable |
| Data backfill needed | Separate script or migration step with comment |

## Composite Primary Keys

Junction tables (`campaign_members`, `collection_items`) use `@@id([...])` per `docs/02_DATABASE_SCHEMA.md`. Factories must supply both key parts.

## JSONB Columns

`Character.abilityScores`, `HomebrewItem.data`, `AuditLog.metadata` — no DB check constraint. Application validates on write; migration only adds column type `Json`.

## Nullable vs Required Rollout

Safe pattern for NOT NULL on existing table:

1. Migration: add nullable column.
2. Backfill in seed or data migration step.
3. Second migration: `SET NOT NULL`.

Single PR only if table is new/empty.

## CI Migration Path

CI test job runs `migrate deploy` against test DB — committed SQL must apply cleanly on empty DB. Avoid destructive renames without data migration SQL in same file.

## Troubleshooting

| Error | Fix |
| --- | --- |
| P3006 migration failed | `migrate resolve`; fix SQL; new migration |
| Drift detected | `prisma migrate diff` — do not `db push` in shared env |
| Seed FK violation | truncate order or create parent entities first |
| Enum value missing in TS | sync `packages/shared` + regenerate client |

## Post-Migration Code Touch List

```
[ ] apps/api/src/**/*.service.ts — new fields
[ ] packages/shared — types/Zod
[ ] test/factories/*.ts
[ ] docs/02 — column list
[ ] apps/web — only if UI displays field (separate FE PR ok)
```

